<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278764>
    dc:description "PLATE 111. A, B. Male genitalia. C. Scutum + metathorax + propodeum. D. Chela. A. Gonatopus nearcticus, from Greece. B. G. nigricans, from Malaya. Different shapes of dorsal process of paramere. C, D. G. bicuspis, holotype (from Olmi 1993d). Scale bar 0.14 mm for A and B, 0.40 mm for C and 0.12 mm for D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278764/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278774>
    dc:description "PLATE 114. Gonatopus nigricans, Female. A. From China, Guangdong. Length 2.5 mm. B. Head, from China, Macau (from Olmi 1984). C. Mesoma, lateral view, from China, Macau (from Olmi 1984). D. Chela, from China, Macau (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 1.10 mm for B, 1.02 mm for C and 0.12 mm for D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278774/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

